<br>
Here is the story...<br>
<br>
Last night my lvl 12 cleric (buffed with things i've never seen before) sat peacefully in Paladul Caverns medding her favorite spells when along came a troll shammy.  Unfortunately, this shammy was being attacked by combination of 43 sensates, phlarg fiends and tunnelers when I decided to assist him.  Feeling heroic, I though I would divert the attention and allow him to run away to safety.  I stood up, said a quick prayer to Innoruuk and cast Word of Pain.  Needless to say, this worked rather well.  I managed to cast it a few more times before I had the full attention of all the monsters attacking the shaman.  Fortunately Innoruuk smiled on me and I was able to slay all of the monsters (the 25 pt DS helped too) and even managed to ding 15 1/2.<br>
<br>
Pretty much the funniest thing I have ever seen.  So much fun that by the time I left 30 minutes later I was lvl 19.<br>
<br>
Not to be left out on the action, the shammy (lvl 65) ran around and pretty much trained the entire zone.  I then stood up my main (lvl 53 mage) in the thick of battle and cast scintilation.  Heh.<br>
  47 mobs<br>
  28200 pts of damage<br>
  78 : 1  dam/mana efficiency<br>
  DPS (assuming the 3 sec cast time):  9400 DPS.<br>
<br>
Hilarious and entirely too much fun.  Now I want to try an AE group (if your are on Saryn, let me know).<br>
<br>
Casala, 53 Elementalist of Saryn (not for long!)<br>
